verbose_text: Two loci on chromosomes 5 and 7 are associated with the development of HHT3 (OMIM : # 601101) and HHT4 (OMIM : # 610655), respectively [XREF_BIBR, XREF_BIBR], whereas HHT5 (OMIM : # 615506) is caused by mutations in GDF2 on chromosome 10, coding for bone morphogenetic protein 9 (BMP9).
evidence: HHT5 (OMIM: #615506) is caused by mutations in GDF2
